wikipedia_page.main: Jonathan Bratoëff (born 1974 in France) is a Berlin-based guitarist.Bratoëff is a member and co-founder of the F-IRE Collective. He has released several albums on the F-IRE Collective's own label, and has also played with musicians like Julian Siegel, Soweto Kinch, and Orphy Robinson.

response: Porpoise Corpus is a forward-looking jazz ensemble composed of David O'Brien, Tom Ward, Tom Challenger, Spencer Brown, Jonathan Bratoeff (from the F-IRE Collective) and Guy Wood.
